properties.import_notes: The Taliban and elements of al Qaeda control most of southern Kandahar. The group killed dozens of civilians in a days-long assault on the Kandahar Airfield in December, a major hub for remaining U.S. and NATO troops.

After months of slowly moving into villages surrounding the city, Taliban fighters took control of Kunduz in September, only to be pushed out by Afghan special forces in October after hard fighting. The areas around the city remain contested.

The Taliban seized control of several areas around Sangin in November and December. At times outgunned and outnumbered, Afghan soldiers and police continue to fight to keep the militants from taking the entire district. But other areas have already fallen. The districts of Musa Qala, Kajaki, Nawzad, Gereshk, Baghran, and Dishu have all come under Taliban control or are heavily contested.
